<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#LanguageSupportKind> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Language support kind"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#LanguageSupportKind> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page> <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Programming_language_concepts> .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#MethodologicalApproach> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "class of formal entities that represent methodological orientations, techniques, or styles of treatment used in the study or engineering of software languages and related formalisms"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#MethodologicalApproach> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Methodological approach"@en .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareArtifact> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Software artifact kind used to classify the characteristic artifacts of a technological space"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareArtifact> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Software artifact"@en .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Concrete software languages (e.g., XML, SQL, OWL) are represented as individuals of this class. Language families are represented as subclasses. Artifact kinds capture the kinds of artifacts written in such languages."@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Software language"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareLanguage> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page> <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_language> .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareTool> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Software tool"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SoftwareTool> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page> <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_tool> .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SubjectArea> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "research or application area relevant to the foundations of software languages and related disciplines"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#SubjectArea> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Subject area"@en .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#TechnologicalSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Technological spaces are families of related software-language technologies that share characteristic artifact kinds, metalanguages, tools, conformance relations, skills, and communities of practice. A technological space is not just a single language or formalism, but a working context in which artifacts are defined, manipulated, queried, transformed, validated, exchanged, and executed according to characteristic principles. This class represents such ecosystems."@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#TechnologicalSpace> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Technological space"@en .
# 
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#assertedForConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Relates a reified assertion about language concepts with the concept"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#assertedForConcept> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Asserted for concept"@en .
<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#assertedForConcept> <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/page> <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Programming_language_concepts> .
# 
